Privacy Policy
User Agreement
This agreement (the “Agreement”) sets forth the terms and conditions by which Bad Jump Games offer you access to use and enjoy:
Our game Top Jockey (the “Game”);
The underlying Game software (the “Software”);
Our website topjockey.com (the “Website”); and,
Any other of our apps, websites, games, or services that link to this Agreement, regardless of how you access or use them, including through mobile devices.
While using these products and services we may require you to provide personal info. We retain and use such info according to the terms of our Privacy Policy (the “Privacy Policy”).
Please read the terms of this Agreement carefully. By clicking the “Accept” button below, or by using any of Bad Jump Games services, you agree that this Agreement is enforceable like any written contract signed by you.
YOUR ACCOUNT
1.1 How can I create an account and play?
Playing the Game requires you to:
read and accept the terms of this Agreement;
give permission for your player stat data to be used on our global leaderboard;
download and install a valid copy of the Software;
Register for an account; and
meet the minimum system requirements.
These requirements may change as the Game evolves. You must pay for your own internet connection, equipment, servicing, and any repair costs necessary to access the Game.
ACCOUNT TERMINATION
2.1. How can my account be suspended or terminated?
We can suspend or terminate your account if we determine in our sole discretion that:
you have violated any part of this Agreement, including illegal transferring of coins, account mining, illegal use of multiple accounts, excessive use of inappropriate names or anything else we find to be breaking the rules and detrimental to gameplay.
we have stopped offering the Top Jockey in your region; or
doing so would be in the best interests of our community, Bad Jump Games, or the rights of a third party.
2.2. What happens if my account is suspended?
If your account is suspended, contact Bad Jump Games on Facebook or Twitter to inquire about regaining access to your account.
2.3. What happens if my account is terminated?
If your account is terminated, you’ll no longer have access to it, including any of the associated data or content. You’ll not be entitled to any refunds and we’ll have no liability to you. We also reserve the right to terminate any other accounts you may have created (also without any refunds or liability to you).
You understand and agree that violating these terms comes with the risk that your account may be terminated or suspended and that, whenever you use Top Jockey, you’ll bear this risk in mind and always conduct yourself appropriately.
