VIRTUAL GOODS
4.1. What kind of “virtual goods” can I access in the Game?
When using the Game, you may unlock/purchase horseshoes. You can also win energy, trophies, and horseshoes by winning races.
4.1.1. Coins: Users can acquire “coins” within the app, which can then be exchanged for races and other customizations.
4.1.2. Rubies: Users can acquire “coins” within the app, which can then be exchanged for races and other customizations.
4.1.3. Trophies: Users have the opportunity to win trophies.
4.1.4. Silks: Users have the opportunity to earn silk outfits for their jockey characters.
4.2. Do I “own” the Virtual Goods I unlock?
(No. What you “unlock” is not the virtual good itself, but rather, a qualified right to access it in the Game.)
You have no ownership or other property interest in any of the Virtual Goods you earn or purchase, regardless of whether you acquired access to those Virtual Goods by purchasing or earning them. Virtual Goods have no monetary value. You can’t redeem them for cash. You can’t obtain any refunds for purchasing Virtual Goods, except as expressly permitted by us.
We have the right to delete, alter, move, remove, or transfer any and all Game Content—including Virtual Goods—in whole or in part, at any time and for any reason or no reason, with or without notice to you, and with no liability of any kind to you. We don’t provide or guarantee, and expressly disclaim, any value, cash or otherwise, attributed to any data residing on servers we operate or control, including any Game Content attributed to your account.
